                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Subsidy load weighs on ONGC margin
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          ONGC chairman R.S. Sharma (left) with director (HR) A.K. Balyan in New Delhi on Wednesday. (PTI)                                  
	New Delhi, June 25: Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC) today reported a 2 per cent decline in net profit for the fourth quarter ended March 31, as its subsidy outgo almost doubled during the period.        
	ONGC registered a net profit of Rs 2,627.10 crore for the January-March period compared with Rs 2,681.64 crore in the same period of the previous fiscal, company chairman and managing director R.S. Sharma said.        
	ONGCs share of the subsidy burden rose to Rs 8,472 crore in the fourth quarter of fiscal 2007-08 from Rs 4,668 crore in the same period a year ago. Sharma said the subsidy burden for the full year was Rs 22,001 crore against Rs 17,024 crore in 2006-07.        
	He said that for the current fiscal, the companys outgo was estimated to jump to about Rs 38,000 crore as crude prices have risen to an all-time high.        
	The company posted a 6 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 16,701 crore for the year ended March 31, 2008, compared with Rs 15,642 crore a year ago. During the financial year, ONGCs total income increased to Rs 64,859 crore from Rs 60,875 crore in 2006-07.         
	Oil companies such as Indian Oil, Bharat Petroleum and Hindustan Petroleum faced a Rs 2,45,000-crore deficit for selling fuel before cost before the June 4 hike in fuel the prices.                                                                                                                                                                           
